---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Automated Pallet Wrapping — Formic"
  description="Stretch-wrap cells that consistently wrap, label, and stage finished pallets — running directly from the palletizer to the dock without operator intervention."
  ogTitle="Automated Pallet Wrapping — Formic"
  ogDescription="Stretch-wrap cells, dock-ready. Fully managed under the Formic Full Service model."
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/solutions/pallet-wrapping" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/solutions">Solutions</a><span class="sep">/</span>Pallet Wrapping
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Pallet Wrapping</div>
    <h1>Automated Pallet Wrapping.<br><em>Dock-Ready.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">Stretch-wrap cells that consistently wrap, label, and stage finished pallets running directly from the palletizer to the dock without operator intervention.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/PalletWrapping-Robopac.webp">
        <source src="/Formic-Header.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <span class="dv-cap">Automate NOW · pallet wrapping</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — Why It Matters</div>
      <h2>The wrap is <em>where loads fail</em>.</h2>
      <p>Most pallet damage in transit traces back to inconsistent wrap. Manual wrapping is one of the most variable steps on the floor: film tension, layer count, and corner coverage shift between operators and shifts. Automated pallet wrapping locks all three in, reducing transit damage and film waste across every shift.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Consistent film tension and a programmable wrap profile by SKU</li>
        <li>Fewer transit-damage chargebacks, lower film cost per pallet</li>
        <li>No CapEx — 24/7 support and 100% maintenance included</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="https://land.formic.co/formic-automated-pallet-wrapping" class="larr">Pallet wrapping scoping guide →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/PalletWrapping-Robopac.webp" alt="Formic automated stretch-wrap cell wrapping a finished pallet" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Programmable wrap profile</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0143.jpg" alt="Wrapped, labeled pallet staged at the dock" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Dock-ready · labeled</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — Inline Integration</div>
      <h2>Palletizer to dock, <em>untouched</em>.</h2>
      <p>The wrap cell sits directly downstream of the palletizer on a powered conveyor. Wrap profile auto-selects based on pallet ID; a label printer applies the bill of lading (BOL). The pallet shows up at the dock door already shipping-ready.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Compatible with direct conveyor handoff from palletizer or AMR drop-zone; no operator intervention between wrap and dock</li>
        <li>Auto-select wrap profile from pallet ID or SKU</li>
        <li>Inline print-and-apply labeling option</li>
        <li>Throughput up to 60 pallets/hour, profile-dependent</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">03 — Specs</div>
      <h2>Configurable to <em>any pallet</em>.</h2>
      <p>We spec to your floor space, throughput, and pallet mix. Rotary turntable, rotary arm, or robotic mobile wrapper.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Pallet sizes: 36×36" to 48×48", custom export sizes available</li>
        <li>Stack height: up to 96"</li>
        <li>Film: 60 – 250% pre-stretch, 1 – 6 layers programmable</li>
        <li>Configurations: EtherNet/IP, Modbus TCP, discrete I/O — compatible with most PLC and WMS platforms</li>
        <li>Safety: light curtains, area scanners, full ANSI/RIA R15.06 compliance</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/full-service" class="larr">How Full Service works →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Formic-Pallet-Wrap-Product.jpg" alt="Formic robotic mobile pallet-wrap unit next to a wrapped pallet of cases" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Configurable · scoped to your line</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:80px">
    <div class="db-tag" style="justify-content:flex-start">What's Included</div>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:clamp(32px,4.4vw,64px);font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1.04;color:var(--white);margin:10px 0 14px">One monthly fee. <em style="color:var(--orange);font-style:normal">Everything included.</em></h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.1);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.1);margin-top:14px">
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>System design and cell layout</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>Wrapper, conveyor, and EOAT</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>Print-and-apply labeling hardware</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>Installation and commissioning</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>Wrap profile programming per SKU</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>24/7 monitoring and support</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>All maintenance and parts</div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:24px 24px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:15px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(240,245,241,.85)"><span style="color:var(--orange);margin-right:10px">→</span>Performance SLAs</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Stop losing pallets<br><em>on the truck.</em></h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get a Quote</a>
    <a href="/solutions" class="btn-ctawh">All Solutions</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
